{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "MedicalContraindication",
  "name": "Aspirin in children and teenagers with a viral illness",
  "description": "Aspirin may cause Reye's syndrome (a serious condition in which fat builds up on the brain, liver, and other body organs) in children and teenagers, especially if they have a virus such as chicken pox or the flu."
